<section class="about-section info-section" data-scrollax-parent="true">
	<figure class="figure" data-scroll data-depth="0.7" data-mobile_speed="4" data-scrollax="properties: @figureParallax"></figure>
	<div class="section-content" data-scroll data-depth="1.2">
		<article class="section-article">
			<p>
				<span class="kicksware">Kicksware</span> is designed <b>by and for</b> the sneakerheads to be a modular, all-in-one, end-to-end e-commerce platform as a part of the luxury fashion worldwide ecosystem.
			</p>
			<p>
				It capable of providing opportunity, place, and services not only to a passionate buyer or a prosperous seller
				but those who encourage authenticity, sustain individuality
				and seeking like-minded personalities to further cooperation and collaboration.
			</p>
			<p>
				And although <span class="kicksware">Kicksware</span> has the potential to become both a commercial and production-ready platform to pursue those goals,
				it is actually intended to be a <b>noncommercial research</b> project dedicated to showcasing and support
				the use of modern, cloud-native, up-and-coming, pushing edge technologies
				in the context of the nowadays fashion industry
				while making its part in building a better, more comfortable, more authentic, and more creative ecosystem.
			</p>
			<p>
				However, it is entirely possible for it to evolve into something more in the indefinite future.
				Therefore, <span class="kicksware">Kicksware</span> will continue to exist to adopt new, even more groundbreaking technologies
				while never stop being completely <a href="https://github.com/timoth-y/kicksware-platform">open-source</a>.
			</p>
		</article>
		<a class="hand-wrapper" href="@handIllustrationCredit" target="_blank" data-direction="1">
			<img class="hand-asset" src=@($"{Environment.FileStoragePath}/assets/hand-air-max-90-3.png") alt/>
		</a>
	</div>
	<a class="window-asset" href="@windowIllustrationCredit" target="_blank"
		data-scroll data-depth="1.5" data-scrollax="properties: @windowAssetParallax">
		<img src=@($"{Environment.FileStoragePath}/assets/window-air-max-97.png") alt/>
	</a>
</section>
<section class="about-section title-section" id="who" data-scrollax-parent="true">
	<div class="section-cover" style="background-image: url(@Model[3])" data-scrollax="properties: @coverParallax"></div>
	<div class="section-content" data-scrollax="properties: @titleParallax">
		<h1 class="section-title">WHO?</h1>
		<hr/>
		<h4 class="section-subtitle">«THE ONE»</h4>
	</div>
</section>
<section class="about-section info-section" data-scrollax-parent="true">
	<figure class="figure" data-scroll data-depth="0.7" data-mobile_speed="4" data-scrollax="properties: @figureParallax"></figure>
	<div class="section-content" data-scroll data-depth="1.2">
		<article class="section-article">
			<div id="mobile-bio-trigger" style="position: absolute; top: -300px;"></div>
			<p>
				Before describing the story behind the creation and explanation of Kicksware's mission and goals, it will be appropriate
				for you to get familiar with its creator while discovering some essential information about me:
			</p>
			<p>
				My name is <strong>Timothy Yalugin</strong>. I'm a Ukraine-based full-stack software engineer specializing in designing,
				developing, and maintaining complex, scalable web applications, and cloud solutions.
				I'm also moving towards Software Architecture in my career path as it is my long-term goal for the future.
				As for today, I am in constant search of experience working with new diverse technologies, tools, languages,
				workflows, and projects to gain fundamental knowledge for designing even more complex,
				more secure, and more groundbreaking software infrastructure systems.
			</p>
			<div id="bio-trigger"></div>
			<p>
				If you happen to have a project that can interest me, please continue scrolling to the last section of this page.
				Otherwise, this all is about letting you know that exactly passion for creating,
				building, and discovering new was the main reason for <span class="kicksware">Kicksware</span> to exist.
			</p>
		</article>
		<a class="hand-wrapper" href="@handIllustrationCredit" target="_blank" data-direction="-1">
